ides a 2-approximation, and this is tight. Together, our study\nprovides fundamental understanding of the miniSOS objective function and makes\na step toward the characterization of randomized SP facility location\nmechanisms.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 8 Aug 2011 17:47:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 3 Apr 2012 19:33:10 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 3 Jul 2012 18:06:25 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Sat, 26 Oct 2013 20:34:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-10-29"}
